# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/14-carrot-cafe] 14 Carrot Cafe is a family-operated restaurant serving American cuisine for breakfast and lunch in the Hines Public Market Building on Eastlake Avenue, near the intersection with East Lynn Street, in Seattle's Eastlake neighborhood.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/14-carrot-cafe] The Infatuation's Aimee Rizzo has described 14 Carrot Cafe as a diner and a greasy spoon that is "charming in a nothing's-been-updated-since-1977 kind of way, based on the old photo collages, vintage dining tables, and coin-operated Runts dispensers that definitely nobody uses".
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/14-carrot-cafe] The menu has included biscuits and gravy, cinnamon rolls, egg dishes, "Tahitian" French toast with tahini, crab cake benedicts, hash browns, carrot cake and carrot pancakes, as well as mimosas and carrot juice.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/14-carrot-cafe] In 2009, 14 Carrot Cafe hosted the street food startup Tako Truk.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/14-carrot-cafe] The *Not for Tourists Guide to Seattle* says of 14 Carrot Cafe: "Typical breakfast fare that's, well, typical.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/14-carrot-cafe] Popular anyway." 14 Carrot Cafe was included in *USA Today*'s 2017 list of Seattle's ten best cafes.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] The American restaurant 2120 operates in Seattle's Denny Triangle, near the Amazon Spheres.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] Megan Hill of *Eater Seattle* has described the food as "Latin American-Northwest mash-up" that "[leans] heavily on Pacific Northwest-sourced produce, seafood, and meat".
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] She has also said 2120 has "plenty of industrial moodiness".
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] KING-TV has said the restaurant serves "artful, and detail oriented" food and has a "modern, yet cozy" atmosphere.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] The menu has included chicken with mole negro, grilled octopus, lamb tartare, a Painted Hills strip steak with cilantro chimichurri, Chinook salmon with salsa verde, and masa dumplings.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] The deviled eggs have chapulines (toasted grasshoppers).
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] The wagyu burger has manchego from Beecher's Handmade Cheese, as well as avocado, bacon, and chipotle.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] 2120 has also served macaroni and cheese with duck-fat croutons, bacalao cakes, chile rellenos, and migas.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] Beer, cocktails, and wine are on the drink menu.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] The Gin Wabbit has carrot, egg whites, lemon, and vanilla, and the Sotol Sazerac had agave, fennel bitters, and sotol.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] Owner Milan Uzelac and chef Derek Bugge opened the restaurant on June 24, 2017.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] 2021 initially served lunch and dinner, later launching brunch on July 1.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] According to *Eater Seattle*, Bugge "infuses plates with influences from his native Seattle and from his mother’s Mexican roots".
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] In February 2018, executive sous chef Rusty Cole became executive chef and junior sous chef Kyle Quinn became chef de cuisine.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] Christopher Saenz was the general manager and wine director as of 2019–2021.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] In 2018, 2120 participated in the Choose to Include campaign, which raised funds and awareness for the Special Olympics ahead of the Special Olympics USA Games.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] 2120 has been described as a sibling restaurant of 99 Park in Bellevue, which closed in 2017.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/2120-restaurant] Megan Hill included 2120 in *Eater Seattle*'s overview of the city's "most beautiful" new restaurants of 2017.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/35th-north] Owner Tony Croghan opened 35th North in Seattle's University District in 2001.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/35th-north] The business has operated from Pike and 11th since 2003.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/35th-north] Croghan participated in a contest to build DIY skate spots.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/35th-north] In 2017, the city of Seattle sued 35th North for creating a bowl on Duck Island in Green Lake Park, which the city considers a wildlife habitat.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/35th-north] The *Not for Tourists Guide to Seattle* says the shop has a "comprehensive selection of goods for co-ed skaters".
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/35th-north] In 2018, Tobias Coughlin-Bogue of *Curbed Seattle* called 35th North Seattle's "main skate shop".
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/35th-north] *Thrasher* has described the business as "central Seattle's longest standing core shop".
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/35th-north] Esther Hershkovits included the business in Red Bull's 2022 list of the city's three best skate shops.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] 8oz Burger & Co is a burger restaurant in Seattle.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] The original location operated at the intersection of Broadway and Union in the Harvard Market shopping center, and an outpost operates in Ballard.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] According to Tasting Table, 8oz Burger & Co sources meat from Royal Ranch in the Columbia Basin.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] The restaurant's signature beef burger has Hill's bacon, balsamic onions, Beecher's cheddar, arugula, and truffle aioli on a brioche bun.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] The PB & J Burger has tomato jam, bacon, cinnamon spiced peanut butter, and fontina on a pretzel bun.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] The Pike has habanero jam and the Union has an espresso-rubbed patty.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] Other burgers have braised pork belly, peppercorn aioli, and jalapeño jam.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] The Ballard location serves beer and cocktails, and has hosted happy hour.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] 8oz Burger & Co also offers short rib poutine and milkshakes; varieties include green tea nutella, snickerdoodle, and alcoholic options.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] 8oz Burger & Co was formerly part of the restaurant chain 8oz.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] Burger Bar, which has operated in Los Angeles, Louisiana, and Miami.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] According to *Seattle Metropolitan*, owner Kevin Chung "initially intended to be part of the 8oz. group, but when that partnership didn't gel, he already had the name in place and felt it was easier to just move ahead with it".
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] With a unique menu, Chung opened the first 8oz Burger & Co as 8oz.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] Burger Bar in January 2012, shortly after a previously announced opening date of December 2011.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] The restaurant launched happy hour in February 2012.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] After Chung made plans to open an outpost in Ballard, both locations became known as 8oz Burger & Co.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] The second location opened in 2014, in the space previously occupied by Hamburger Harry's.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] In January 2024, Chung announced plans to close the Broadway location.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] He attributed the closure to rising labor and rent costs, as well as safety concerns.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] Tyrone Beason of *The Seattle Times* said the wild-boar burger was among the best he had ever tasted*.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] Seattle Metropolitan* has said, 8oz Burger's namesake burger "is why we adore this duo of homegrown burger shops.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] But the buffalo burger, and other novelty combos, is why we admire it.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] Throw in hormone-free and grass-fed beef, perfect vanilla shakes, fries that hail from uber-flavorful Kennebec potatoes, and you have a local find, in two locations that do the Great American Meal proud".
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] The magazine's Allecia Vermillion included the business in a 2022 overview of the city's best burgers.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] Dylan Joffe included 8oz Burger & Co's Kennebec fries in *Eater Seattle*'s 2016 overview of the city's best French fries.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] Writers for the *Seattle Post-Intelligencer* included the restaurant in a 2022 overview of the city's best burgers.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] The website's Jay Friedman included 8oz Burger & Co in a 2023 list of fifteen eateries for "mind-blowing" burger in the city.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/8oz-burger-co] Tasting Table's Annie McKay included the business in a 2024 list of the twenty "absolute best" burgers in Seattle.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/a-hong-kong-kitchen] The Chinese restaurant A+ Hong Kong Kitchen is located in Seattle's Chinatown–International District.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/a-hong-kong-kitchen] The menu has included fish balls in curry, rice with minced pork and salted fish, rice rolls, congee, noodle soups, pork chops and spaghetti, pineapple buns, and tea sandwiches with butter and condensed milk.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/a-hong-kong-kitchen] Hoi Ning Chim manages the restaurant as of 2022.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/a-hong-kong-kitchen] Callie Craighead included A+ Hong Kong in the *Seattle Post-Intelligencer*'s 2020 list of "10 top-rated Chinese restaurants in Seattle's International District, according to Yelp".
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/a-hong-kong-kitchen] In 2022, Zuri Anderson of iHeart said the restaurant offers Washington's best Chinese take-out.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/a-hong-kong-kitchen] Aimee Rizzo and Carlo Mantuano included A+ Hong Kong in The Infatuation's 2022 list of "The Best Restaurants in the International District".
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/a-hong-kong-kitchen] The business was also included in the website's 2025 list of the 25 best restaurants in the Chinatown–International District.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/a-hong-kong-kitchen] Caitlin Flynn selected the restaurant for Washington in Eat This, Not That's 2022 overview of "The Best Chinese Takeout in Every State".
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/a-hong-kong-kitchen] In 2022, Jay Friedman included A+ Hong Kong in *Eater Seattle*'s list of "19 Knockout Restaurants in Seattle's Chinatown–International District", and he and Jade Yamazaki Stewart included the business in a list of "20 Knockout Chinese and Taiwanese Restaurants in the Seattle Area".
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abigail-hall] Abigail Hall is a cocktail bar in downtown Portland's Woodlark Hotel, named after Abigail Scott Duniway.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abigail-hall] Brooke Jackson-Glidden of *Eater Portland* said the bar "pairs its floral walls and pink accents with distinguished-looking armchairs and leather booths, covering its counters and mantle with candles.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abigail-hall] Even with a somewhat-vintage look, Abigail Hall is usually buzzing, with its guests pouring refills of martinis between handfuls of fries." The bar hosts high tea.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abigail-hall] Jennifer Quist, Daniel Osborne, and Doug Adams opened the bar in late 2018.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abigail-hall] Jordan Michelman of *Eater Portland* included Abigail Hall in a 2021 list of "9 Portland Hotel Bars Ideal for a Mid-Week Drink".
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abigail-hall] The website's 2021 overview of "Where to Eat and Drink in Downtown Portland" says, "Abigail Hall feels like a cosmopolitan lounge, the kind of place where you'd go for high tea or shrimp cocktails (hint: Abigail offers both).
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abigail-hall] At the pink swirling booths that curl through the bar, customers order martinis for the table alongside oysters on the half-shell, before a Manhattan and a burger (or maybe just a pile of chicken strips and fries)".
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abigail-hall] Katrina Yentch of *Portland Monthly* included the bar in a 2022 list of "The Six Best Portland Spots for Booze Free Drinks".
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abyssinian-kitchen] The restaurant's menu includes lamb in garlic and ginger and tilapia with serrano peppers; the vegetarian sampler has collards and lentils.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abyssinian-kitchen] Abyssinian Kitchen opened in southeast Portland's Hosford-Abernethy neighborhood in 2015.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abyssinian-kitchen] In 2020, the restaurant closed during the COVID-19 pandemic.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abyssinian-kitchen] The business reopened at a new location on Northeast Alberta Street in the Concordia neighborhood in August 2022.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abyssinian-kitchen] In 2016, Michael Russell included Abyssinian Kitchen in *The Oregonian*'s list of the city's ten best new restaurants.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abyssinian-kitchen] He later included Abyssinian Kitchen in his 2017 overview of the 40 best restaurants in southeast Portland, and ranked Abyssinian Kitchen number 38 in his 2019 list of Portland's 40 best restaurants.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abyssinian-kitchen] Russell ranked the business number 23 in *The Oregonian*'s 2025 list of Portland's 40 best restaurants.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abyssinian-kitchen] In 2017, Martin Cizmar included Abyssinian Kitchen in *Willamette Week*'s list of Best Restaurants on Portland's Division and Clinton Streets.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/abyssinian-kitchen] In 2019, Alex Zielinski of the *Portland Mercury* wrote, "The tangy, fresh, and filling plates are enough to keep curious first-timers coming back for seconds." Maya MacEvoy included the restaurant in *Eater Portland*'s 2022 overview of "exceptional" Ethiopian food in the city.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli] Founder and owner Justin King opened the original restaurant on Sandy Boulevard in northeast Portland's Roseway neighborhood in 2019.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli] A second location opened on Northeast Alberta in the Vernon neighborhood.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli] In 2022, the shop was vandalized by someone who spray-painted a swastika on a sign.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli] Locations have operated in San Diego and Oceanside.
[src:ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli/ben-esther-s-vegan-jewish-deli] An outpost operated on Seattle's Capitol Hill.
